<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A frantic search is underway to find two young girls who went missing earlier this week.</p>

<p>The girls, aged five and nine, were last seen after being dropped at a man's house at Nambour, on the Sunshine Coast.</p>

<p>They were last seen around 9.30am on Tuesday. </p>

<p>The girls, aged five and nine, (pictured) were last seen after being dropped at a man's (pictured) house at Nambour, on the Sunshine Coast</p>

<p>A 41-year-old man, who is known to the girls, has also been reported missing. </p>

<p>The man is believed to be driving a white 2019 Great Wall dual-cab utility, with Queensland registration 00CDH.   </p>

<p>Anyone who has seen the man or girls or the car, or has knowledge of their whereabouts is being urged to contact police immediately.</p>

